Something that I’ve been trying to be mindful of lately is discerning the difference between my ego being triggered and my soul.
I’ve been taking the time to evaluate a situation that’s upsetting to me and really see what part of me is upset. 
If my ego is triggered, then what notion do I need to stop clinging to, what is weighing me down? 
If it’s my soul that feels pain, what is begging to be healed?
I find that this has made it easier for me to let go of people and circumstances that represented an egoic attachment or I was clinging to as the result of an unhealed soul wound. 
It’s incredibly freeing to not only allow yourself to feel everything as you feel it and accept it but to also understand it fully- both it’s roots and it’s current manifestation, so that you can finally let go of all the heavy things you’ve been carrying for far too long and start living a more peaceful  life. 
You don’t need to cling to a past version of yourself, you don’t need to let the same situations and people continue to hurt you. Understand where your soul is guiding you and what your ego is holding you back from and allow yourself to break free from past patterns..

My happiness wasn’t given to me by my husband. Is he apart of it? Absolutely. But I worked so hard to stand on my own two feet. To love myself, see my worth, and value all that I am. I found happiness in my walking away from my broken engagement. I found happiness in distancing myself from toxic friends and family members. I found my happiness in building this platform to inspire you all to commit to loving and respecting themselves so that you could attract the love they deserve.

There are a lot of things and people that contribute to my happiness, but without a doubt, this happiness that I feel now, that I’ve worked so hard for, and that I protect, is everything. I did that. After learning to love myself entirely, a man came along who ALSO loved me entirely and added to my happiness. Don’t ever for a second think that happiness is a gift given from someone else. If happiness does come from a single person, that single person is you. 😘❤️💯 Rp via the sister @iamdaliasmith 👈
